The paper discusses the design of transceivers for compact wireless devices with multiple antennas, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also addresses the impact of coupling on bandwidth, which is related to system dynamics and control (cs.SY). The use of circular arrays and diversity techniques suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and radio frequency (cs.RF) systems.
